    "body": "### Problem\n\nCursor highlight doesn't change depending on language mapping.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nCreate the file `cursor.lua`:\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nvim.o.termguicolors = true\r\n\r\nvim.api.nvim_set_hl(0, 'Cursor', { bg = '#0000ff' })\r\nvim.api.nvim_set_hl(0, 'lCursor', { bg = '#ff0000' })\r\n\r\nvim.opt.guicursor:append('a:Cursor/lCursor')\r\nvim.o.keymap = 'greek'\r\nvim.o.iminsert = 1\r\n```\r\n\r\nRun `nvim --clean -u cursor.lua`\r\nCursor is blue, but it should be red.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nCursor should have color of `lCursor` if lmap is on (`vim.o.iminsert = 1`).\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.9.0\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\ncan't say, don't have vim\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.28.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nArch Linux official repository",
